# Skipped by Makefile.workflow's generic build: scanner.
#
# sdlc follows the same per-binary build convention as ../nous: build via a
# dedicated `make sdlc-build` target that writes to cmd/sdlc/bin/sdlc and
# symlinks bin/sdlc → ../cmd/sdlc/bin/sdlc. The generic `make build`
# scanner intentionally leaves bin/sdlc alone so the symlink convention
# isn't accidentally replaced by a real file.
#
# Today sdlc has no signing / notification requirements that strictly
# demand this layout (unlike nous, which is signed + notarized and would
# break keychain ACL grants if overwritten). The convention is held
# anyway because:
#
#   1. Future sdlc features may add notification or other code-signing-
#      sensitive surfaces (e.g., a "harness of harnesses" that sends OS
#      signals). Establishing the per-binary build convention now keeps
#      future migrations cheap.
#   2. Convention parity with nous makes the cmd/<name>/ pattern
#      consistent across ariadne-style repos.
#
# To build sdlc: `make sdlc-build`.
# To install it on PATH: `make sdlc-bootstrap`.
